article.description: Matt Ryan registered 18 points and eight rebounds as Chattanooga defeated VMI 71-64 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Ryan scores 18 to lead Chattanooga past VMI 71-64
article.linkText: Ryan scores 18 to lead Chattanooga past VMI 71-64
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. -- Matt Ryan registered 18 points and eight rebounds as Chattanooga defeated VMI 71-64 on Wednesday night. Maurice Commander had 15 points and six rebounds for Chattanooga (18-12, 9-8 Southern Conference). Trey Doomes added 13 points and seven rebounds. Ramon Vila had 12 points and seven rebounds. Sean Conway had 15 points for the Keydets (8-22, 3-14). Kamdyn Curfman added 12 points. Louis Tang had six rebounds. Travis Evee, the Keydets' leading scorer heading into the matchup at 13 points per game, scored only 6 points on 3-of-11 shooting. Garrett Gilkeson, who was second on the Keydets in scoring heading into the matchup with 11 points per game, was held to 4 points. He was 0 of 4 from 3-point range. The Mocs improve to 2-0 against the Keydets for the season. Chattanooga defeated VMI 86-67 on Feb. 12. Chattanooga finishes out the regular season against UNC Greensboro at home on Saturday. VMI finishes out the regular season against Samford on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
